@sdwheeler Thanks.  The first blog post fixed it for me.  It appears that the one remaining PSRL still named `PSReadline` was in my `Windows PowerShell` Modules folder. 

<img width="631" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5177512/177843955-6e74fba4-4fe3-4f7a-b147-6df850b9a5ba.png">

Once I renamed that folder to `PSReadLine`, `Update-Help PSReadLine -Force` worked just fine from pwsh.
